Lesson #1 in toilet seat etiquette.  If you leave the seat up, the bathroom light on, the door open, the toothbrush on the sink instead of the toothbrush holder, then it's not my fault if your baby brother finds his way easily into the bathroom, grabs your toothbrush and swirls it in the toilet.  What do we learn from this?  To do what your momma said.  Your toothbrush goes back in the toothbrush holder on the wall above the sink, you put the seat and lid down, you turn off the light and you shut the door.  This is not hard.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src=http://www.sethmountaineers.com/eq/lesamlammindcontrol.jpg><br>
